direct the concerned persons to produce the documentary requirements as soon as possible, to avoid the audit suspension maturing into a disallowance; 
direct the Business Permit and Licensing Office to fast-track the completion of the database in order for the BPLS to be fully operational and request explanation for the delay;
stop the practice of procuring computer software programs unless actual needs and demands are first considered such as the hardware, people-ware and other technical requirements;
conduct actual inspection on the percentage of project completion and request for refunds on the excess payments;
consider blacklisting the supplier for its failure to complete the project.

